To handle multiple karats (14, 18, 22, etc.) and convert them for Kiran (24kt), you should use a "Bucket" Ledger and a Conversion Voucher.

1. The Ledger (The Bucket)
Create one single ledger to group all your purchases:

Ledger Name: Old Gold Stock (Mixed Karats)
Nature: ASSET
Key Setting: Allow Quantity: YES.
How to use: Whenever you buy gold from a customer (whether it is 18kt or 22kt), record it into this one ledger. The "Quantity" will track the total gross weight you have in the shop.
2. The Voucher (The Conversion)
Since you need to "turn" this mixed gold into 24kt for Kiran, you need a Voucher to move the weight.

Voucher Type: Create a new one called GOLD CONVERSION (Nature: JOURNAL).
3. The Template (The Calculation)
Create a template called "Convert to Fine (24kt)":

CR (Credit): Old Gold Stock (Mixed Karats) -> Put the Full Weight you are melting (e.g., 10g of 22kt).
DR (Debit): Gold Stock – Fine -> Put the Calculated 24kt Weight (e.g., 9.16g).
Why this is better?

Grouping: You don't need 10 different ledgers for 14kt, 18kt, etc. One "Mixed" ledger keeps your reports clean.
Tracking: You can always see exactly how much "Mixed" weight you have waiting to be melted.
Accuracy: Once converted to the Gold Stock – Fine ledger, it is ready to be used in your KIRAN OUT – Repay Gold templates.